    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.31a-31b_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection
                    62-2</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">31a</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Route 1
                        Columbia, Mo.
                        Oct. 27, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You and your program continue to be a light shining brightly every day you come to my house. It's<sic>Its</sic> warm glow continues from one telecast to the next!</p>
                
                <p>I read, and re-read "To Sigurd", since my work and recreation is children. In your Epic I see so much description which is child-like, with the true wisdom of children, in its clarity and its truth. I wonder if you have written poems especially for these
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26c.31a-31b_0002"/>
               
                <fw type="curatorial">31b</fw>
                    
                    young and wise.</p>
                    
                <p>With the wisdom of your writing and the beauty of your words you make sense of the jumble of thoughts and feelings in us all. So, again, thank you for sharing yourself and your life with us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mrs. Ted Fisher</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
